    "content": "nullSales Performance Management\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Sales Performance Management\n Sales Planning\n Sales Planning Setup\n Data Sources Management\n Create a Sales Plan\n Segmentation\n Territory Planning\n Implementing Territory Planning\n Importing Data for Planning Territories\n Designing Strategic Territories\n Aligning Territories to Reach Leadership’s Goals\n Plan Territories for In-Person and Virtual Business\n Assigning Units Based on Rules and Criteria\n Distributing Units Based on Your Company’s Metrics\n Designing Territories with Visualizations Using Overlays\n Keeping Territories Running Smoothly\n Quota Planning\n Quota Attainment Planning\n Legacy Sales Planning\n Incentive Compensation Management\n Release Notes for Sales Performance Management\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALES PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT\nPlan Territories for In-Person and Virtual Business\n\nDesign territories that include a mix of contiguous and noncontiguous areas in Territory Planning. Give all your sales and service reps opportunities to meet customers in person and remotely when you limit assignments within an area. Indicate whether to assign more or fewer units or containers to an area relative to others within the focus.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Web Services API enabled\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo manage alignments:\tSalesforce Maps Territory Planning permission set license and SF Maps Territory Planning permission set\nOpen an alignment and set the focus. Select an area or a container that you want to set up for virtual meetings.\nSet the geographic profile to Noncontiguous. If you want to assign more or fewer units or territories to an area relative to others within the focus, change the balance percentage. For example, to assign the territory 10% more units relative to other territories in the focus, enter 110. To assign 15% fewer units, enter 85.\nRepeat the previous step for at least one more area or territory.\nSave your changes.\nClick Optimize. To ensure that all your reps get a share of assignments, limit assignments to areas by an attribute such as annual revenue.\nSet your optimization priority, then optimize your focus.\nThe optimized focus with your contiguous and noncontiguous areas appears on the map.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
